However hideous and un-kissing fresh these Gothic beasts exhibit absolute grace and poetry in flight.  The first time I ever experienced a California condor my wife and I were traveling on a mountain road on a ridge and at a small saddle between two canyons a large deep, dark shadow in the sky slowly and silently cruised over us.
